Several factors are at the root of this overall deterioration in the food insecurity situation observed between June  and June . This is mainly due to the sharp rise in the armed conflict in the  since , particularly in  and , and clashes in  and . These conflicts have caused new displacements of populations and further deteriorated household food security. The  “Common Narrative for the fight against malnutrition estimates” about 6 million malnourished children and 7.2 million women with anemia confirming the magnitude estimated by the IPC analysis;
The number of health areas in alert increased from 7.5% in  to 14% in ;
Low health coverage for pregnant, breastfeeding women and in particular for children, in addition to a rural economy limited to subsistence ; 
Nearly 50% of corn production losses due to fall armyworm and other crop pests; 
General poverty in  limiting financial access to basic services and certain food groups rich in animal protein.

The 10th analysis cycle on the Integrated Food Security Phase Classification undertaken in December  revealed that 6.7 million people are classified in Phases 3 (Crisis) and 4 (Emergency) and are in urgent need of humanitarian assistance. In comparison with the 9th cycle of June, food security has globally experienced a slight deterioration and remains very worrying in certain territories, particularly  in "",  in , ,  and  in the . The proportion of people facing food security crisis and emergency situation is estimated at 11% of the . The  shows that 5  are in emergency phase (phase 4), 68  are facing food crisis situation (phase 3) and  are under pressure, in phase 2. The causes of food insecurity in  are:
the persistence of armed group operations
violence perpetrated by armed groups and the aftermath of military operations in the ;
the high prevalence of acute malnutrition which affects a large proportion of children aged less than 5 years;
the inadequate food consumption of poor families in terms of poor calorific value and unbalanced;
diseases and various natural disasters (climate perturbations, flood, problem in rain patterns, landslides especially); with a more or less important impact on crops, livestock, and infrastructure. Moreover, it is worth noting that the causes of food insecurity in  are various and diversified and closely related to the generalized poverty of rural population. The entire , in , almost experiences a lack of basic infrastructure and general problems related to rural development.

